scurry /ˈskʌrɪ/

(scurrying,scurried,scurries) 

1. V-I When people or small animals scurry somewhere, they move there quickly and hurriedly, especially because they are frightened. (尤指因受惊而) 急促跑 [书面] 

例： The attack began, sending residents scurrying for cover. 袭击开始了，使得居民们急促奔跑寻找藏身之处。

